cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.HC 

The paper deals with modelling page view dynamics on Wikipedia, which involves analyzing user behavior and content popularity. This could fall under several sub-categories, but the most likely ones are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as they both deal with analyzing user behavior and content popularity. Additionally, cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) could also be relevant, as they deal with software systems and their impact on society. Finally, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) could also be a possible sub-category, as the paper discusses the circadian cycles of users and how they affect content popularity.
